This paper is about a machine learning algorithm for time series classification, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves ensembles of classifiers, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of tree-structured classifiers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE), but can also be applied to time series data.
